<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A person who is trained to give
first aid and other emergency medical assistance in the absence of a
physician, and to assist a physician in the administration of health
care. Paramedics are often associated with police, firefighting units,
or rescue squads.</def>⟦br⟧
